An assistant chief in Marsabit was on Thursday sentenced to 20 years in prison for defiling his 15-year-old -daughter at Kiturini in March. Emmanuel Lengolei was sentenced in a Marsabit court for defiling the Standard Five girl. Witnesses, including the girl, narrated how the father defiled her. Senior magistrate Tom Wafula found there was evidence of defilement. A medical report was presented in court. Lengolei was found to have sexually abused his daughter between March 26 and 27 this year. The accused denied the charge. He was given 14 days to appeal. Click here for the latest political news